<br>
Even funnier to hear enchanters whining about the difficulties of finding a group.  But what do your misconceptions of the ranger class have to do with the point he's brought up that there's something imbalanced about a caster class being able to completely and unequivocably replace any melee class in a group setting just by standing out of melee range of the engaged mob?<br>
<br>
Do I care if you can solo with a charmed mob?  As long as you aren't leapfrogging, kill-stealing, or dumping your trains of added trash on me, I don't care what you solo.  Offhand, I can't think of any caster class that doesn't solo better than rangers overall.  But something I will point out in regards to soloing... if wizards, necromancers, and druids got the nasty unannounced surprise of mobs suddenly becoming unsnareable, what makes you think that charm capable classes are somehow exempt from the unwritten prohibition that you aren't supposed to be soloing extensively?<br>
<br>
Personally I don't care for the proposed change or consider the ability to charm a level 60+ mob overpowered.  After all, if you're going to drudge up the fact that mobs do more damage now, then don't forget to include the fact that all classes do more damage as well and have infinitely more hit points than they did in previous expansions.  But I suspect the change has more to do with the fact that Verant didn't take into account the possibility that charmed mobs would be used extensively in these &quot;high end&quot; encounters.  But I doubt that even an NPC with a 1% slow effect will suddenly not outdamage rogues and monks.<br>
<br>
<br>
Salta states:  &quot;If people didn't simply go buy their c3 in the nexus and go solo/duo for kicking exp in FG all day long while crappy dps classes like chanters had nothing better to do I think you might have a few less bitter chanters.&quot;<br>
<br>
Let's place the blame of that where it belongs, at the feet of the enchanters who (still) do nothing but sell castings of c3 all day long.  And odd but I saw a fair amount of enchanters in AE groups or soloing with a dire charmed mushroom or fungusbeast in Fungus Grove when I soloed there.  <br>
