<br>
You misunderstand.<br>
<br>
Command of Druzzil has, on live servers, a -50 to the resist check vs. magic when cast for the target to resist.  (Loosely translated, if a creature has a 200 sv Magic score, they check at a MR score of 150 against CoD.)<br>
<br>
<br>
Part of the original change to the spells was to reduce the resist check modifier down to -10 for Command of Druzzil (and complete removal from the other classes' version), as well as the addition of 1% slow to the charmed mob.  These changes were done on Test only.  On the Test server, the 1% slow and resist modifier changes were removed from the spells this morning.  The Test version of Command of Druzzil now works the same as the live server versions.<br>
<br>
Of note:  Command of Tunare, Word of Terris, and Call of the Archmage have had their potential maximum duration increased to a possible 20.5 minutes at level 65 on Test.  So it's pretty obvious that they're not done playing around with the spells just yet. <br>
<br>
<br>
